<TITLE> 31 Hizb-ut Tauhid men arrested in Kushtia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kushtia, April 17 (bdnews24.com)  Thirty-one suspected militants, including the alleged district chief of Islamist outfit Hizb-ut Tauhid, were arrested in the town Friday noon. They were arrested from their office 'Pother Disha' at Lohapotti of Boro Bazar in the town. "They were arrested while holding a secret meeting. Some leaflets, Jihadi literature, some CDs and some explosives were seizedfrom them," said Babuluddin Sarkar, officer-in-charge of Sadar Police Station. However, Hizb-ut Tauhid district chief Mahbub Ali said they were discussing the rules of prayer in the meeting. bdn
